153typedef struct UiObject_ {
154 char fname[200]; /*< \todo document this */
155 char command[200]; /*< \todo document this */
156 bool firstRun; /*< If this UiObject has been put through the
157 user interaction processor. */
158 EmbVector controlPoints[10]; /*< Storage for however many Rubber Points the
159 design needs. */
160 char controlPointLabels[10][200]; /*< Storage for the labels for the Rubber Points
161 using the same indexing. */
162 int n_controlPoints; /*< The number of entries in the controlPoints
163 and controlPointsLabels. */
164 int numPoints; /*< The number of points if we consider the object as a Polygon. */
165 int minPoints; /*< The minimum number of points needed to make the
166 polygon look somewhat like the design. */
167 int maxPoints; /*< The maximum number of points before adding more will
168 do nothing but slow down the program. */
169 EmbVector center; /*< Where the polygon is centered. */
170 EmbVector scale; /*< The scale of the object: note that the default
171 may not be (1.0, 1.0). */
172 EmbReal rotation; /*< \todo document this */
173 unsigned int mode; /*< The mode argument records what kind of design we are
174 using and how to interact with it. */
175 char path_desc[1000]; /*< The SVG style path spec. */
176 char text[200]; /*< The text to be rendered to the scene. */
177 int textJustify; /*< One of the JUSTIFY_* constants representing what kind
178 of alignment to use. */
179 char textFont[200]; /*< The file name of the font to use. */
180 float textHeight; /*< The text height. */
181 float textRotation; /*< The rotation of the text in the scene. */
182 //GLuint texture_id; /*< Pointer to a texture that may be rendered to the object. */
183 char id[200]; /*< \todo document this */
184 int pattern_index; /*< \todo document this */
185 char type[200]; /*< \todo document this */
186 int object_index; /*< \todo document this */
187 bool selectable; /*< \todo document this */
188 EmbColor color; /*< \todo document this */
189} UiObject;

694static const EmbReal emb_constant_pi = 3.14159265358979323846;
695
696/*
697 * \brief Convert \a a to a QPointF.
698 */
699inline QPointF
700to_QPointF(EmbVector a)
701{
702 QPointF result(a.x, a.y);
703 return result;
704}
705
706/*
707 * \brief Convert \a a to an EmbVector.
708 */
709inline EmbVector
710to_EmbVector(QPointF a)
711{
712 EmbVector v;
713 v.x = a.x();
714 v.y = a.y();
715 return v;
716}
717
718/*
719 * \brief Wrapper for embVector_add to use the syntax \a a + \a b.
720 */
721inline EmbVector
722operator+(EmbVector a, EmbVector b)
723{
724 return embVector_add(a, b);
725}
726
727/*
728 * \brief Wrapper for embVector_subtract to use the syntax \a a - \a b.
729 */
730inline EmbVector
731operator-(EmbVector a, EmbVector b)
732{
733 return embVector_subtract(a, b);
734}
735
739inline EmbReal
740radians(EmbReal degrees)
741{
742 return (degrees*emb_constant_pi/180.0);
743}
744
748inline EmbReal
749degrees(EmbReal radian)
750{
751 return (radian*180.0/emb_constant_pi);
752}
753
757class BaseObject : public QGraphicsPathItem
758{
759public:
760 BaseObject(QGraphicsItem* parent = 0);
761 virtual ~BaseObject();
762
763 enum { Type = OBJ_TYPE_BASE };
764 virtual int type() const { return Type; }
765
766 QPen objPen;
767 QPen lwtPen;
768 QLineF objLine;
769 int objRubberMode;
770 QHash<QString, QPointF> objRubberPoints;
771 QHash<QString, QString> objRubberTexts;
772 qint64 objID;
773
774 qint64 objectID() const { return objID; }
775 QPen objectPen() const { return objPen; }
776 QColor objectColor() const { return objPen.color(); }
777 QRgb objectColorRGB() const { return objPen.color().rgb(); }
778 Qt::PenStyle objectLineType() const { return objPen.style(); }
779 EmbReal objectLineWeight() const { return lwtPen.widthF(); }
780 QPainterPath objectPath() const { return path(); }
781 int objectRubberMode() const { return objRubberMode; }
782 QPointF objectRubberPoint(const QString& key) const;
783 QString objectRubberText(const QString& key) const;
784
785 QPointF objectCenter() const { return scenePos(); }
786 EmbReal objectCenterX() const { return scenePos().x(); }
787 EmbReal objectCenterY() const { return scenePos().y(); }
788
789 void setObjectCenter(EmbVector center)
790 {
791 setPos(center.x, center.y);
792 }
793 void setObjectCenterX(EmbReal centerX) { setX(centerX); }
794 void setObjectCenterY(EmbReal centerY) { setY(centerY); }
795
796 QRectF rect() const { return path().boundingRect(); }
797 void setRect(const QRectF& r) { QPainterPath p; p.addRect(r); setPath(p); }
798 void setRect(EmbReal x, EmbReal y, EmbReal w, EmbReal h) { QPainterPath p; p.addRect(x,y,w,h); setPath(p); }
799 QLineF line() const { return objLine; }
800 void setLine(const QLineF& li) { QPainterPath p; p.moveTo(li.p1()); p.lineTo(li.p2()); setPath(p); objLine = li; }
801 void setLine(EmbReal x1, EmbReal y1, EmbReal x2, EmbReal y2) { QPainterPath p; p.moveTo(x1,y1); p.lineTo(x2,y2); setPath(p); objLine.setLine(x1,y1,x2,y2); }
802
803 void setObjectColor(const QColor& color);
804 void setObjectColorRGB(QRgb rgb);
805 void setObjectLineType(Qt::PenStyle lineType);
806 void setObjectLineWeight(EmbReal lineWeight);
807 void setObjectPath(const QPainterPath& p) { setPath(p); }
808 void setObjectRubberMode(int mode) { objRubberMode = mode; }
809 void setObjectRubberPoint(const QString& key, const QPointF& point) { objRubberPoints.insert(key, point); }
810 void setObjectRubberText(const QString& key, const QString& txt) { objRubberTexts.insert(key, txt); }
811
812 virtual QRectF boundingRect() const;
813 virtual QPainterPath shape() const { return path(); }
814
815 void drawRubberLine(const QLineF& rubLine, QPainter* painter = 0, const char* colorFromScene = 0);
816
817 virtual void vulcanize() = 0;
818 virtual QPointF mouseSnapPoint(const QPointF& mousePoint) = 0;
819 virtual QList<QPointF> allGripPoints() = 0;
820 virtual void gripEdit(const QPointF& before, const QPointF& after) = 0;
821protected:
822 QPen lineWeightPen() const { return lwtPen; }
823 void realRender(QPainter* painter, const QPainterPath& renderPath);
824};

889class CircleObject : public BaseObject

891public:

893 CircleObject(CircleObject* obj, QGraphicsItem* parent = 0);

897 void updatePath();
898
899 enum { Type = OBJ_TYPE_CIRCLE };
900 virtual int type() const { return Type; }
901
902 QPainterPath objectSavePath() const;
903
904 EmbReal objectRadius() const { return rect().width()/2.0*scale(); }
905 EmbReal objectDiameter() const { return rect().width()*scale(); }
906 EmbReal objectArea() const { return emb_constant_pi*objectRadius()*objectRadius(); }
907 EmbReal objectCircumference() const { return emb_constant_pi*objectDiameter(); }
908 QPointF objectQuadrant0() const { return objectCenter() + QPointF(objectRadius(), 0); }
909 QPointF objectQuadrant90() const { return objectCenter() + QPointF(0,-objectRadius()); }
910 QPointF objectQuadrant180() const { return objectCenter() + QPointF(-objectRadius(),0); }
911 QPointF objectQuadrant270() const { return objectCenter() + QPointF(0, objectRadius()); }
912
913 void setObjectRadius(EmbReal radius);
914 void setObjectDiameter(EmbReal diameter);
915 void setObjectArea(EmbReal area);
916 void setObjectCircumference(EmbReal circumference);
917
918 void updateRubber(QPainter* painter = 0);
919 virtual void vulcanize();
920 virtual QPointF mouseSnapPoint(const QPointF& mousePoint);
921 virtual QList<QPointF> allGripPoints();
922 virtual void gripEdit(const QPointF& before, const QPointF& after);
923protected:
924 void paint(QPainter*, const QStyleOptionGraphicsItem*, QWidget*);
925};
